from many in the publishing industry. The winner, selected from an original 130, will be announced on October 11. The shortlist for the Booker, the UK's most hyped literary prize and one of the most lucrative, is all the more surprising in a bumper year for new fiction fulfilling the criteria - English language and non-American - for consideration for the award. But if the shortlist of the final six candidates for the prize may be disappointing, the traditional controversy surrounding the award is as rife as ever. According to one insider, some on the list 'are B-team writers at best'. 